              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.6"
              stroke-linecap="round"></path><circle
              cx="12"
              cy="16.7"
              r="1.05"
              fill="currentColor"></circle></svg
          > macOS – Unsigned App
        </h3>
        <p class="m-0 text-[0.68rem] leading-[1.55] text-text-secondary">
          First launch may be blocked because the app is not code‑signed.
          Allow it once:
          <br />1. Double‑click the app: when the warning appears, click <strong
            >Cancel</strong
          > (or <strong>Done</strong>).
          <br />2. Open <strong
            >System Settings → Privacy & Security</strong
          > and scroll down.
          <br />3. Click <strong>Open Anyway</strong> next to the blocked app
          notice.
          <br />4. Confirm (enter password) when prompted. Future launches
          are allowed until you update to a new binary.
          <br />This is a normal macOS Gatekeeper step for unsigned
          open‑source builds.
        </p>
      </div>
